        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 6:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 619 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles east of Gatlinburg, or 9 miles southwest of Smoky Mountains-Big
Creek, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Smoky Mountains-Balsam Mountain, Smoky Mountains-Oconaluftee, Smoky
Mountains-Cataloochee, B.R. Parkway-Smoky Mountains To Balsam Gap,
Cherokee, Smoky Mountains-Big Creek, and Smoky Mountains-Newfound
Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
